&#8220;Motorsport is a hobby in our country. Gugu had to literally hold down three, four jobs at one time; we both had to work hard. There are not millions that I am sitting on. &#8220;People actually think that I am sitting on millions because I get random emails from people asking me to help them financially since my husband passed away, and I&#8217;m like, &#8216;are you kidding me?'&#8221; Letshego told Cliff Central in an interview. Gugu died while attempting to summit Mount Kilimanjaro last year. He left behind his widow, Letshego and their daughter. Listen to the full interview below Content hosted by iono.fm For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.